<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8" />
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0" />
  <title>Interactive Website by Iranzi Delyce</title>
  <style>
    body {
      font-family: Arial, sans-serif;
      margin: 0;
      padding: 0;
      background: #f5f5f5;
      transition: background 0.3s, color 0.3s;
    }
    header {
      background: #4A6CF7;
      padding: 20px;
      text-align: center;
      color: white;
    }
    .container {
      max-width: 900px;
      margin: 20px auto;
      background: white;
      padding: 20px;
      border-radius: 8px;
      box-shadow: 0 0 10px rgba(0,0,0,0.1);
    }
    button {
      padding: 10px 15px;
      background: #4A6CF7;
      color: white;
      border: none;
      border-radius: 5px;
      cursor: pointer;
      transition: 0.2s;
    }
    button:hover { background: #3554c9; }
    .dark-mode { background: #1e1e1e; color: #e0e0e0; }
    #image-box {
      width: 100%;
      height: 220px;
      background: url('https://picsum.photos/800/300') center/cover;
      border-radius: 8px;
      margin-top: 10px;
    }
    input, textarea {
      width: 100%;
      padding: 10px;
      margin: 8px 0;
      border: 1px solid #bbb;
      border-radius: 5px;
    }
    .error { color: red; font-size: 14px; }
  </style>
</head>
<body>
  <header>
    <h1>Interactive JavaScript Website by Iranzi Delyce</h1>
    <p>Welcome to my small interactive website project, created by Iranzi Delyce. I made this page to practise JavaScript in a simple and real way.</p>
  </header>

  <div class="container">
    <h2>1. Theme Switcher</h2>
    <p>This button lets you switch the website theme. Personally, I like dark mode more — but you can choose what feels comfortable for you.</p>
    <button onclick="toggleTheme()">Toggle Dark/Light Mode</button>
  </div>

  <div class="container">
    <h2>2. Image Change Button</h2>
    <p>I added this feature because I enjoy visuals. Press the button and see a new random image — like a little surprise each time.</p>
    <div id="image-box"></div>
    <button onclick="changeImage()">Change Image</button>
  </div>

  <div class="container">
    <h2>3. Contact Form with Validation</h2>
    <form onsubmit="return validateForm()">
      <label>Your Name (so I know who you are)</label>
      <input type="text" id="name" placeholder="Enter your name" />

      <label>Your Email (for replies)</label>
      <input type="text" id="email" placeholder="Enter your email" />

      <label>Your Message</label>
      <textarea id="message" placeholder="Type your message..."></textarea>

      <p class="error" id="error"></p>
      <button type="submit">Submit</button>
    </form>
  </div>

  <script>
    function toggleTheme() {
      document.body.classList.toggle('dark-mode');
    }

    function changeImage() {
      const img = `https://picsum.photos/800/300?random=${Math.floor(Math.random()*1000)}`;
      document.getElementById('image-box').style.backgroundImage = `url(${img})`;
    }

    function validateForm() {
      let name = document.getElementById('name').value.trim();
      let email = document.getElementById('email').value.trim();
      let message = document.getElementById('message').value.trim();
      let errorBox = document.getElementById('error');

      if (name === '' || email === '' || message === '') {
        errorBox.textContent = "All fields must be filled out.";
        return false;
      }
      if (!email.includes('@')) {
        errorBox.textContent = "Email must contain @ symbol.";
        return false;
      }

      alert("Thank you! Your form has been submitted.");
      return true;
    }
  </script>
</body>
</html>
